 NUKE v. 1. To intentionally delete the entire contents of a given directory
or storage volume. "On UNIX, rm -r /usr will nuke everything in the usr
filesystem." Never used for accidental deletion. Oppose BLOW AWAY. 2. Syn.
for DIKE, applied to smaller things such as files, features or code sections.
3. Used of processes as well as files; frequently an alias for "kill -9" on
UNIX.